### .NET version

All up to 7.0

### Did it work in .NET Framework?

No

### Did it work in any of the earlier releases of .NET Core or .NET 5+?

No

### Issue description

This `propertyGrid1.SelectedObject = new Params();` will save `p1` and `p2` changes even after Cancel button pressed.
```cs
  public class Params
  {
      public List<P> List { get; set; } = new List<P>() { new P() };
  }

  public class P
  {
      public int p1 { get; set; }
      public int p2 { get; set; }

      public override string ToString()
      {
          return $"{p1}, {p2}";
      }
  }
```


https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/assets/17767561/2d98239d-0f28-431e-b005-47adb9461608

The problem is here (`_originalItems[i]` is the same object as `Items[i]`):
https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/blob/bbe3f455171e0158a2238282d30d001d2fdda5c6/src/System.Windows.Forms.Design/src/System/ComponentModel/Design/CollectionEditor.CollectionEditorCollectionForm.cs#L768-L773
and then here:
https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/blob/bbe3f455171e0158a2238282d30d001d2fdda5c6/src/System.Windows.Forms.Design/src/System/ComponentModel/Design/CollectionEditor.CollectionEditorCollectionForm.cs#L278-L284

